<h2 id="search-campaign">4. Searching for a campaign</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>To search for campaigns, select the search parameters in the <strong>Orders » Coupons</strong> menu. If you do not change the default filter settings, all of the campaigns are searched for and displayed. A search filter for coupon codes is available in the <a href="/en/orders/managing-orders#1370">order search</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Searching for a campaign:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Orders » Coupons</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Filter</strong> area, enter the ID or the coupon code or select the filter options in the drop-down lists. Note the explanations in <a href="#table-search-campaign">Table 4</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Search</strong> (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The campaigns that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
